Aim:
To check whether a given number is a palindrome.

Algorithm:
Start
Input n
temp = n, rev = 0
While temp > 0
rem = temp % 10
rev = rev × 10 + rem
temp = temp / 10
If rev == n → palindrome
Else → not palindrome
Stop

Program:
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int main(){
    int n, temp, rev = 0;
    cout<<"Enter a number: ";
    cin>>n;

    temp = n;
    while(temp > 0){
        rev = rev*10 + temp%10;
        temp /= 10;
    }

    if(rev == n)
        cout<<"Palindrome Number";
    else
        cout<<"Not Palindrome";

    return 0;
}

Sample Output:
Enter a number: 121
Palindrome Number

Result:
The program checks whether a number is palindrome.
